<item>
            <title>[LS-96] 7.10 Partial Re-Generation Logic</title>
                <link>https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-96</link>
                <project id="10099" key="LS">Laxy Studio</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Epic:&lt;/b&gt; 
    &lt;span class=&quot;jira-issue-macro&quot; data-jira-key=&quot;LS-84&quot; &gt;
                &lt;a href=&quot;https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-84&quot; class=&quot;jira-issue-macro-key issue-link&quot;  title=&quot;Epic 7: Guide &#8212; Audio Generation&quot; &gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;icon&quot; src=&quot;https://laxy.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/universal_avatar/view/type/issuetype/avatar/10307?size=medium&quot; /&gt;
            LS-84
        &lt;/a&gt;
                                                    &lt;span class=&quot;aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-complete jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf&quot;&gt;To Do&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Goal:&lt;/b&gt; Provide granular Partial Re-Generation logic at the ADK Orchestrator level to ensure that editing a single error or adjusting a single audio parameter does not trigger a costly and time-consuming complete batch run.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Requirements:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Item &amp;amp; Language Level API Isolation:&lt;/b&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The ADK pipeline trigger endpoints (e.g., &lt;tt&gt;POST /pipeline/resume&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;/pipeline/generate-audio&lt;/tt&gt;) must explicitly accept an optional payload filter: &lt;tt&gt;spotIds: string[]&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;languages: string[]&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;When these parameters are present, the Orchestrator must strictly scope its execution &lt;em&gt;only&lt;/em&gt; to the targeted spot-language combinations, never defaulting to the full venue collection.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Sub-Component Execution (Smart Skip Logic):&lt;/b&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Re-generation must isolate sub-components to save Token costs.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;If a Creator explicitly edits &lt;em&gt;only&lt;/em&gt; the &lt;b&gt;Director Note&lt;/b&gt; manually, the pipeline should skip the &lt;tt&gt;s7_voice_recommend&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;s8_director_note&lt;/tt&gt; LLM calls, and route directly to &lt;tt&gt;s9_audio_gen&lt;/tt&gt; (TTS generation).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;If a Creator triggers a segment-level fix (via 
    &lt;span class=&quot;jira-issue-macro&quot; data-jira-key=&quot;LS-93&quot; &gt;
                &lt;a href=&quot;https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-93&quot; class=&quot;jira-issue-macro-key issue-link&quot;  title=&quot;7.7 Audio Evaluation UI (n6_audio_qa)&quot; &gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;icon&quot; src=&quot;https://laxy.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/universal_avatar/view/type/issuetype/avatar/10315?size=medium&quot; /&gt;
            LS-93
        &lt;/a&gt;
                                                    &lt;span class=&quot;aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-complete jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf&quot;&gt;To Do&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/span&gt;
), the system strictly executes the &lt;tt&gt;guide.audio_fix&lt;/tt&gt; prompt and skips the macro script enhancement steps.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Data Persistence &amp;amp; Adjacent Spot Safety:&lt;/b&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;When a targeted generation is running, adjacent SpotMetadata documents in Firestore must remain completely untouched and preserve their existing &lt;tt&gt;pipelineStageStatus&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;active&lt;/tt&gt; audio versions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;For the targeted spot, its &lt;tt&gt;pipelineStageStatus.gate3&lt;/tt&gt; automatically reverts to &lt;tt&gt;pending&lt;/tt&gt; (if previously approved) while the new generation runs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Unit Economics &amp;amp; Cost Saving Structure:&lt;/b&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;ai_cost_log&lt;/tt&gt; must log token usage specifically tagged with the executed &lt;tt&gt;spotId&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;stepId&lt;/tt&gt;, proving that the token burn was strictly limited to the micro-edits.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Acceptance Criteria:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;[ ] The Audio Generation API endpoint successfully accepts and strictly respects &lt;tt&gt;spotIds&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;languages&lt;/tt&gt; payload arrays.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;[ ] Triggering a single-spot generation completely ignores adjacent spots, preserving their database state and storage assets.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;[ ] Smart Skip Logic works: Modifying a downstream parameter (like TTS Voice) re-runs the TTS engine without pointlessly re-running upstream text prompts (like Director Note or Script Enhance).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;[ ] The UI correctly reflects the &quot;Generating...&quot; loading state &lt;em&gt;only&lt;/em&gt; on the specifically targeted items.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;[ ] Total API token counts logged in Firestore for a partial re-generation strictly represent the isolated sub-components and targeted spots, proving cost isolation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
